    <title>QPS crashing on some hardware (hyperthreading-related?)</title>
    <link>https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/qps-crashing-on-some-hardware-hyperthreading-related/1588</link>
    <description>Hi  there,

I have noticed that QPS, the system tool that displays and manage processes, installed by default cannot work when the CPU mitigation file is loaded by GRUB (/etc/default/grub.d/40_cpu_mitigations.cfg).

Once this configuration file isn&#39;t loaded by GRUB, the application QPS works fine.</description>
    
